Hey Avgeeks!! 🤓. Check that off of my bucket list ✅ Visiting my favourite car manufacturer while on days off in Germany 🙏. Would also love to thank @audi for putting my symbol on their signage 😁. So here we go!!!! Story Time Part 3: The last part of this story focused on my inspiration and how my parents supported me from inception to where I am today. It also is the story about how #royalcanadianaircadets #aircadets came into my life and how much time my mother dedicated to driving me around for meets/parades, community events and summer camps. For all you young Avgeeks in 🇨🇦, I highly recommend you get into this amazing organization 👌. It taught me so much as well as shaping me and giving me the confidence I have today. During my teens, I always knew I wanted to be a pilot and with the cadets and all of the aviation activities I did only solidified my mind that I was on the right track. My high school days were very similar to my childhood and I drew airplanes in class, was always looking up to the sky and forward to the weekend with my dad at the airport or an air cadet function. By 18 years old I was done high school and two weeks after my final exam I was in Aviation College in Toronto, Canada. I couldn't drink alcohol at the time in Ontario but I could fly and train in airplanes, that was all I needed. Most of my college classmates were going out for drinks after class and training and I couldn't.... I knew what I wanted and pursued it as soon as I could. You guys and girls have the dream, do your absolute best to start today! One day sooner to your dream and goal! 🍾 🙏
